						<summary>

						<p>A slab set up in a street of the same village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vijayaraṅga-Chokkanātha-Nāyaka: Ś. 1650, Kali 4829, Kīlaka, Puraṭṭādi 31, [. .] 10, Tuesday, Aviṭṭam = 1728 A.D., October, 1. The paksha was śukla.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged in some places.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land for worship in the temple of Tiruneḍuṅgaḷanātasvāmi by a certain Subbiramaṇiya-mudaliyār, son of Vaḍamalaiyappa-mudaliyār, the agent of the ruler and one Śambayarāyar. </p>						

						</summary>
